When doing imports to JIRA, clients sometimes do not want all of the data transferred from the source system, in order to keep the imported project relatively clean. In our particular case, we don't want to have lots of closed/resolve bugs getting transferred (although I could see the need to filter based on other criteria).

Although advanced filtering would be great, it would still be nice if we had the ability to simply exclude certain criteria from the transfer. For example, if the field mapping UI were to display a set of checkboxes for each mapped field value(such that we could exclude all issues with a "closed" status, or issues with a "Low" priority), this would go a long way towards solving our problem.

As it stands now, we need to import the entire remote Bugzilla project, and then run a Groovy script later to do the cleanup. This makes the import really slow, and we also have to maintain an extra script.

