When performing a bulk conversion of large number of tickets, the JSON-file can become rather large.

This means, it can bump into Jira's global limit on attachment-size (default is mere 10Mb) and also take a long time to upload. However, JSON files being what they are, gzip compresses them dramatically (15-19 times with gzip -9).

Importer should automatically detect and seamlessly process gzip-ed input files. Supporting other compressors (bzip2, xz) would be nice too, but gzip is the most widespread...

